<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1437,153,677]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,289,400,427]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Biology</emphasis>
. Presumably obtained from a gall of what 
<bibRefCitation author="Fitch, A. M. D." box="[780,921,400,427]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="781 - 829" refId="ref55876" refString="Fitch, A. M. D. (1859) Fifth report on the noxious and other insects of the state of New York. Insects infesting deciduous forest trees. Annual Reports of the New York State Agricultural Society, 18, 781 - 829." type="journal article" year="1859">Fitch (1859)</bibRefCitation>
originally called 
<taxonomicName authority="Fitch, 1859" authorityName="Fitch" authorityYear="1859" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Cynips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quercuspisum">
<emphasis box="[1122,1364,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Cynips quercuspisum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fitch, A. M. D." pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="781 - 829" refId="ref55876" refString="Fitch, A. M. D. (1859) Fifth report on the noxious and other insects of the state of New York. Insects infesting deciduous forest trees. Annual Reports of the New York State Agricultural Society, 18, 781 - 829." type="journal article" year="1859">Fitch, 1859</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(now, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fitch, 1859))" authorityName="Lobato-Vila &amp; Pujade-Villar" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Fitch" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[290,733,436,463]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quercuspisum">
<emphasis box="[290,565,437,463]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Ceroptres quercuspisum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fitch, A. M. D." box="[582,715,436,463]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="781 - 829" refId="ref55876" refString="Fitch, A. M. D. (1859) Fifth report on the noxious and other insects of the state of New York. Insects infesting deciduous forest trees. Annual Reports of the New York State Agricultural Society, 18, 781 - 829." type="journal article" year="1859">Fitch, 1859</bibRefCitation>
))
</taxonomicName>
according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Osten-Sacken, C. R. von" box="[895,1197,436,463]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="331 - 380" refId="ref57049" refString="Osten-Sacken, C. R. von. (1865) Contributions to the natural history of the Cynipidae of the United States and of their galls. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Philadelphia, 4 (3), 331 - 380." type="journal article" year="1865">Osten-Sacken (1865: 370)</bibRefCitation>
, on the underside of leaves of 
<taxonomicName box="[263,417,472,499]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis box="[263,417,472,499]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Quercus alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName box="[469,653,472,499]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="46" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="section">
<emphasis box="[469,563,473,499]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Quercus</emphasis>
section
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Osten-Sacken, C. R. von" box="[678,904,472,499]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="47 - 72" refId="ref57009" refString="Osten-Sacken, C. R. von. (1861) On the Cynipidae of the North American oaks and their galls. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Philadelphia, 1 (3), 47 - 72." type="journal article" year="1861">Osten-Sacken 1861</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Osten-Sacken, C. R. von" box="[926,1219,471,498]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="331 - 380" refId="ref57049" refString="Osten-Sacken, C. R. von. (1865) Contributions to the natural history of the Cynipidae of the United States and of their galls. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Philadelphia, 4 (3), 331 - 380." type="journal article" year="1865">Osten-Sacken (1865: 369</bibRefCitation>
, 370) says the gall from which 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Osten-Sacken" authorityYear="1865" baseAuthorityName="Osten-Sacken" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[288,388,508,534]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pisum">
<emphasis box="[288,388,508,534]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">C. pisum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was obtained could be induced, in fact, by 
<taxonomicName authority="(Osten-Sacken, 1862)" baseAuthorityName="Osten-Sacken" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[874,1404,507,534]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Acraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pezomachoides">
<emphasis box="[874,1150,508,534]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Acraspis pezomachoides</emphasis>
(Osten-Sacken, 1862)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1437,153,677]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,543,569]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Osten-Sacken" authorityYear="1865" baseAuthorityName="Osten-Sacken" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[324,510,544,570]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pisum">
<emphasis box="[324,510,544,570]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Ceroptres pisum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from a single specimen (
<bibRefCitation author="Osten-Sacken, C. R. von" box="[1090,1361,542,569]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="47 - 72" refId="ref57009" refString="Osten-Sacken, C. R. von. (1861) On the Cynipidae of the North American oaks and their galls. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Philadelphia, 1 (3), 47 - 72." type="journal article" year="1861">Osten-Sacken 1861: 59</bibRefCitation>
), a female, which Osten-Sacken erroneously stated to be a male in the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Osten-Sacken, C. R. von" box="[1139,1424,578,605]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="331 - 380" refId="ref57049" refString="Osten-Sacken, C. R. von. (1865) Contributions to the natural history of the Cynipidae of the United States and of their galls. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Philadelphia, 4 (3), 331 - 380." type="journal article" year="1865">Osten-Sacken 1865: 369</bibRefCitation>
), so he redescribed it. We found and examined the only 
<typeStatus box="[761,809,615,641]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Osten-Sacken" authorityYear="1865" baseAuthorityName="Osten-Sacken" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[960,1060,614,640]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Ceroptres" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pisum">
<emphasis box="[960,1060,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">C. pisum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is deposited in MCZ; it is pierced through the mesosoma, thus preventing us from studying the median groove.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
